			<div class="description col six">
				<p><a href="./">Lokshahi</a></p>
				<p><em>2008-2009</em></p>
				<p><em class="background">&ndash; An e+m-Governance venture for rural citizens in India.</em></p>
				<br />
				<p>Lokshahi facilitates citizens to lodge complains, monitor complain status and prioritize community complaints using SMS on low-cost mobile devices. The platform is designed for rural citizens and works in vernacular languages. The government officials and citizens can also access the platform on the web. An appreciation-based incentive mechanism is built-in for well-performing government officials.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><b>role:</b> Conceptualization, User Research, Interaction Design, Platform Architect, Software Development.</p>

<p><b>skills:</b> Java – J2EE, WAS, DB/2, algorithms for rankings, frontend development.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><b>+</b> Platform deployed in Solapur, India – a constituency with 200,000 rural citizens.</p>

<p><b>+</b> Entire platform is open-sourced. 24 man-months effort.</p>

<p><b>+</b> Won the highly competitive IBM The Great Mind Challenge 2009 award amongst 13,000 teams.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/ppl2point0/" target="new">Project on SourceForge.</a></p>

